# HackFarmer — Cursor AI Rules

## What this project is
A multi-agent system that generates complete hackathon projects from spec documents.
Users upload a PDF or describe their project in text. Seven AI agents run in a
directed graph (LangGraph) and produce: working frontend + backend code, a README,
a reveal.js pitch deck, and a Mermaid architecture diagram. Output is pushed to a
new GitHub repo and available as a ZIP download. Users authenticate via GitHub OAuth
and bring their own LLM API keys (Gemini, Groq, OpenRouter).

## Tech stack — never suggest alternatives to these
Backend:    FastAPI + Python 3.11 + SQLAlchemy + SQLite + alembic
Agents:     LangGraph (StateGraph) — 7 nodes, strict topology
LLM:        openai SDK (unified — works with Gemini, Groq, OpenRouter)
Auth:       GitHub OAuth 2.0 + JWT in httpOnly cookies (hf_session)
Encryption: cryptography.fernet for GitHub tokens and user API keys
Real-time:  sse-starlette (Server-Sent Events — NOT WebSockets)
Vectors:    chromadb (local, in-process) + sentence-transformers (local, CPU)
Frontend:   React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS + Framer Motion + Zustand + React Router
Icons:      lucide-react only
UI prims:   @radix-ui/react-* for accessible dialogs, tooltips, progress
Animations: framer-motion only — no CSS keyframes in JS, no GSAP
Code view:  react-syntax-highlighter
Diagrams:   mermaid (npm) — rendered in browser, not server-side
File drop:  react-dropzone
Pitch deck: reveal.js HTML string (generated by business agent, sanitized with bleach)
Automation: n8n self-hosted (Docker) — webhook triggers only, never in critical path

